snippet.title: Java Language Futures - All Aboard Project Amber by Brian Goetz
snippet.description:
The accelerated release cadence for the Java platform offers us many more opportunities for delivering new features -- and we plan to do just that. Join Java Language Architect Brian Goetz on a whirlwind tour of the language features under development in Project Amber.

# Brian Goetz
Brian Goetz is the Java Language Architect at Oracle, and was the specification lead for JSR-335 (Lambda Expressions for the Java Programming Language.) He is the author of the best-selling Java Concurrency in Practice, as well as over 75 articles on Java development, and has been fascinated by programming since Jimmy Carter was President.
